I believe that ,if it hasn't already been done, it's important that you know that you will always meet people who won't necessarily agree with your choices, who won't like your style, your facial expressions or whatever else... but, never stop believing in yourself, stay true to yourself, with your personality and sensitivity that convinced the jury; Another thing, it's not given to everyone to dare! It will allow you to move forward and we can only see that you fit in with any repertoire, I even find your versions sometimes better than the original! You seem humble and deeply kind, you have talent and generosity, you were not part of what I would have bet on at the beginning and sincerely, I can't remember not having enjoyed one of your performances, you surprise me... to finish, I loved your interpretation of Gainsbourg, I had also loved the original but for once I could hear the lyrics clearly , we had maybe the impression that you were careful not to make any facial expressions, you transmitted emotion to me through my television so I don't understand why 3 members of the jury didn't feel it! That's it, I wish you lots of good things, stay grounded, don't change anything about what you are, stay humble, stay you, use constructive criticism and don't pay attention to the ones that aren't.
